u told Jahaar, 'sorry to bother you again, one more quick question. Do you know who returned the Paladin AA ability Divine Stun?'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:39:14 2002] You told Jahaar, 'retuned'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:39:44 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'yeah, what's up?'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:40:27 2002] You told Jahaar, '2 min cast time seems to defeat the purpose.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:40:42 2002] You told jahaar, 'since most casting mobs immediately recast when interrupted'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:41:29 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'I'll look into it some more.  I'm not really happy with what it's doing now'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:41:42 2002] You told Jahaar, 'The idea for how it was meant to be seemed really good'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:41:53 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'it had some problems the old way'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:41:56 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Obviously some technical issues stopped it working though.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:42:11 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'like if you mem 4 stuns you can just keep uber mobs stunned non stop'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:42:38 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Would it be possible to make it only interrupt? and uber mobs it wont apply too since they are above level 61'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:43:18 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'only interrupt is a good idea'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:43:19 2002] You told Jahaar, 'The places i see it useful are the big temple in Cazic Thule... The lizards cheal and are above level 55. Seems like a great use for the AA there, also a great place would be Ring of Fire.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:43:59 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Paladins really dont care about the stun part, the interrupt is the key part now. Which is why many paladins are use cease and desist now and not the high level stuns.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:45:13 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Anyway thanks for the consideration. Nice to know its easy to talk to you about some of the small issues.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:45:22 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Have a good night.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:46:27 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'sorry had to go afk a sec'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:47:09 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'I want that ability to be good for paladins, but I think that the level 55 stun cap is pretty out of date... I don't like that you can be fighting an exp mob and not be able to stun it by normal methods'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:47:39 2002] You told Jahaar, 'The stun part really isnt an issue for most paladins. We dont mind it, but interrupt is important to us'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:47:55 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'as soon as I find a good solution that lets the AA be useful, and also lets people stun exp mobs then I'll do it for sure'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:47:57 2002] You told Jahaar, 'We feel its a class defining capability'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:48:06 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'yes, it is and is for clerics also'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:48:18 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Yes keeps clerics happy too.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:48:40 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'I was playing in new CT the other night and had to wait for one of the Thul Tae Ews to run out of mana after CHing himself 8 times because we couldn't stun'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:48:46 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'I didn't like it much'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:48:53 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Exactly what prompted me to come here and tell you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  '<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:49:01 2002] You told Jahaar, 'It felt like the perfect use for the skill'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:49:12 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'well, the change on test is going to go live but that doesn't mean it's a finished issue'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:49:22 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'at least if it goes live like this it has some value as opposed to none'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:49:31 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Would it be okay if i passed this info across to the paladin board?'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:49:52 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'if you like, I'm not sure what the resolution will be though'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:50:09 2002] You told Jahaar, 'I think they will be happy to know you are thinking about it. We thought it was a dead issue.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:50:09 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'there are other classes than paladins that get to stun, and I want them all to be valuable when fighting 55+ exp mobs'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:50:49 2002] You told Jahaar, 'You can really trivialise an encounter with stun though'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:51:08 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Mana cost on stun is so low that 2-3 paladins will make it never hit.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:51:49 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'yes, but I'm focusing on exp mobs though with this.  I want to make the divine stun useful in big encounters, and just having it interrupt would be a good use for it.  On top of that though, I want to make the exp group paladin or cleric be '<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:52:08 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'able to interrupt and stun things too.. in situations where there won't be 4 paladins'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:52:37 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Wow thats a very different opinion. I gathered VI hated Stuns on level 61+ mobs'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:52:51 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'interrupts on 61+ would be great'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:53:22 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Possibly considered making divine stun a 3/6/9 type of skill? Starts of working on a certain range and moves up to allow higher and higher level mobs?'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:53:31 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'I don't really want Cazic Thule perma-stunned though and just standing around getting beat on'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:54:00 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Agree, what about toss in a icon on the stunned mob to stop it stacking?'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:54:17 2002] You told Jahaar, 'So stun last 3 seconds but you cant land it again for another 6 seconds?'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:54:22 2002] You told Jahaar, 'because the spell wont hold?'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:54:44 2002] You told Jahaar, 'thatll solve the perma stun issue, will basically just lower the mobs damage output without trivialising the encounter.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:54:45 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'can't really do that for some other reason.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:55:02 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Ok'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:55:17 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'monsters don't have enough debuff slots and that's not an easy fix, so your stun would bounce off because the mob was out of slots due to being slowed, debuffed, etc.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:55:52 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Its not so bad actually. You can either interrupt or have a chance to stun'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:56:04 2002] You told Jahaar, 'just need to choose the spells more wisely'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:56:17 2002] You told Jahaar, 'So many stun spells but so little difference between them.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:56:34 2002] You told Jahaar, 'that could create a reason to use more of them.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:57:56 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'yes, hopefully we'll put up a new solution in the next couple weeks'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:58:15 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Thank you for the chat. Been very interesting.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:58:33 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'sure, sorry I couldn't give you more concrete answers'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:58:49 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Gave me way more. I hope I didnt bother you too much.'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:59:10 2002] Jahaar tells you, 'nope, happy to chat with people when I have the time'<br>[Mon Mar 18 16:59:24 2002] You told Jahaar, 'Have a good night. Bye' <p>Sir <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6665">Gallux</a> the <A HREF="http://everquest.station.sony.com/hht/events/events_mar2001.jsp">Cavalier</a><BR>60 Human <A HREF="http://pub3.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.html">Crusader</a><BR><A HREF="http://www.midnightfury.com">Midnight Fury</a><BR><A HREF="http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.html">Erollisi Marr</a><BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugallux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallux</A> at: 3/17/02 11:28:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://w