t). <br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Enchanters also have these other 6 spells which have a minor stun component</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Chaotic Feedback, Sanity Warp, Chaos Flux, Anarchy, Discordant Mind, Dementia)<br><br>Other classes also have access to some minor Stuns, but these 4 classes have Stun as a core ability where they get a whole line of spells.<br><br>I'm not saying that Paladins don't deserve something good to work with for high level stuns, my point is that I'd be foolish to overlook the importance of stuns for any of these 4 classes.<br><br>-Rich <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upraetorthecrusader.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Praetor the Crusader</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 193<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/02 12:31:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=62.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My chat with Rich Waters and the changes to Divine Stun.</span><hr size=1> You missed Quellious Words of Tranquility, Rich. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>By the way...  Now that we have your attention, QWoT is stunning only for the same duration as Force.  Not 10 seconds as listed. <p><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=16699" style="text-decoration: none">Praetor, 60th Crusader</a></b><BR><a href="http://www.avatarsofdiscord.org" style="text-decoration: none">Avatars of Discord</a> (site down for repairs)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/c